00:03:09.700 --> 00:03:15.700
The adult brain
crowned by the cerebral cortex.

00:03:15.700 --> 00:03:20.460
A wrinkled mass of tissue just a
fraction of a centimeter thick.

00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:27.230
Within its furrows
lie our powers

00:03:27.230 --> 00:03:30.960
to reason, judge, understand.

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:35.530
But buried beneath
is an unconscious underworld--

00:03:35.530 --> 00:03:37.730
a cluster of structures

00:03:37.730 --> 00:03:42.030
that drives our appetites,
moods and emotions.

00:03:44.930 --> 00:03:50.130
MAN:
For a long time, it was thought
the brain was divided into two.

00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:53.960
Emotion was one thing
and thought was something else,

00:03:53.960 --> 00:03:55.860
and these were two things

00:03:55.860 --> 00:03:58.700
that were interfering
with each other.

00:03:58.700 --> 00:04:00.330
But it's now clear

00:04:00.330 --> 00:04:04.830
that this division was wrong,
just completely wrong.

