00:08:52.630 --> 00:08:54.530
and I'd had that
stupid stroke, you know?

00:08:54.530 --> 00:08:56.800
Yeah.

00:08:56.800 --> 00:09:01.000
NARRATOR:
Emotion: you can see it
on Marvin's face--

00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:04.860
a smile, a laugh,
a scowl of frustration.

00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:09.660
But what he does not experience
is the awareness of emotion.

00:09:16.730 --> 00:09:18.360
Emotions are generated

00:09:18.360 --> 00:09:21.200
by structures hidden deep
in the brain.

00:09:22.900 --> 00:09:25.100
The tiny, almond-shaped amygdala

00:09:25.100 --> 00:09:28.230
is the first to respond
to an emotional event,

00:09:28.230 --> 00:09:31.260
triggering a series
of split-second reactions

00:09:31.260 --> 00:09:33.560
within the brain's
emotional core.

00:09:35.400 --> 00:09:39.560
Waves of nerve impulses
travel down the brain stem,

00:09:39.560 --> 00:09:43.400
setting off an instantaneous,
visceral response

00:09:43.400 --> 00:09:45.100
throughout the body.

00:09:45.100 --> 00:09:49.530
DAMASIO:
A lot of the time, the machinery
that produces the emotion

00:09:49.530 --> 00:09:52.460
is operating
without us noticing it at all,

00:09:52.460 --> 00:09:56.530
creating changes in posture
and in facial expression,

00:09:56.530 --> 00:10:00.860
altering the way the organs
inside the body are working,

00:10:00.860 --> 00:10:04.100
preparing the body
for what's needed next,

00:10:04.100 --> 00:10:06.400
generating chemical responses

00:10:06.400 --> 00:10:08.900
that you will
never know existed,

00:10:08.900 --> 00:10:13.260
and all of this is what
constitutes the emotional state.

00:10:15.600 --> 00:10:17.300
NARRATOR:
For most people,

00:10:17.300 --> 00:10:20.530
awareness of a feeling
follows just milliseconds

00:10:20.530 --> 00:10:23.360
after an emotion is created.

00:10:23.360 --> 00:10:25.200
The body sends signals back

00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:27.600
to the area
of the brain responsible

00:10:27.600 --> 00:10:31.300
for conscious thought,
making us aware of our feelings.

00:10:34.560 --> 00:10:37.400
It is in this region
of emotional awareness

00:10:37.400 --> 00:10:40.800
that Marvin's stroke decimated
hundreds of millions

00:10:40.800 --> 00:10:42.460
of brain cells.

00:10:44.600 --> 00:10:49.030
Marvin experiences emotion,
his body responds.

00:10:49.030 --> 00:10:51.330
But when the physical response

00:10:51.330 --> 00:10:54.560
is communicated back
to his thinking brain,

00:10:54.560 --> 00:10:56.830
the signal falls into a void.

00:10:56.830 --> 00:11:01.900
Marvin can only guess at what he
or others may be feeling.

00:11:03.530 --> 00:11:05.060
