to have him back emotionally.

00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.700
We care about each other,
you know,

00:14:25.700 --> 00:14:30.160
and I'll always love him,
but I just miss the old Marvin.

00:14:35.860 --> 00:14:41.460
DAMASIO:
There's an old idea that emotion
is not at all a good thing,

00:14:41.460 --> 00:14:44.330
because it is difficult
to control.

00:14:44.330 --> 00:14:47.900
But emotion is extremely useful.

00:14:47.900 --> 00:14:50.600
Emotion is not a luxury.

00:14:50.600 --> 00:14:54.260
Emotion is part and parcel
of the mechanisms

00:14:54.260 --> 00:14:56.700
that allow us to stay alive.

00:15:03.130 --> 00:15:08.760
NARRATOR:
Feelings seem intangible,
intensely subjective.

00:15:08.760 --> 00:15:13.000
But now, using
new imaging technologies,

00:15:13.000 --> 00:15:15.360
scientists have demonstrated

00:15:15.360 --> 00:15:18.930
that emotions have a physical
place in the brain.

00:15:18.930 --> 00:15:22.360
Anger...

00:15:22.360 --> 00:15:25.830
Happiness...

00:15:25.830 --> 00:15:29.860
Sadness...

00:15:29.860 --> 00:15:31.230
Fear.

00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:36.130
Sometimes intense,
often fleeting,

00:15:36.130 --> 00:15:38.700
each has a specific
neural circuitry

00:15:38.700 --> 00:15:42.500
that has evolved over
millions of years.

00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:48.100
Why do we have
these emotional states?

00:15:48.100 --> 00:15:49.860
What are they for?

00:15:49.860 --> 00:15:51.960
Well, they all serve a purpose.

00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:53.960
They're all adaptive.

00:15:53.960 --> 00:15:56.900
By having a feeling of emotion,

00:15:56.900 --> 00:16:02.660
you have a possibility of taking
into account what happened

00:16:02.660 --> 00:16:07.160
and using that for the proper
planning of future actions.

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:11.130
If something caused happiness,

00:16:11.130 --> 00:16:15.300
because it was something that
was potentially good for you,

00:16:15.300 --> 00:16:19.760
having that feeling is going to
help you organize your planning

00:16:19.760 --> 00:16:22.860
around the possibility
of getting some more

00:16:22.860 --> 00:16:25.230
of that good thing that you had.

00:16:27.560 --> 00:16:30.960
NARRATOR:
Even emotions
that are disturbing,

00:16:30.960 --> 00:16:34.060
like anger or fear,
have their purpose.

00:16:34.060 --> 00:16:36.530
MAN:
No one's life
is free from stress,

00:16:36.530 --> 00:16:39.660
and when those stresses occur
or problems arise,

00:16:39.660 --> 00:16:41.630
we have specific emotions

00:16:41.630 --> 00:16:44.400
that are part of our repertoire
for a reason,

00:16:44.400 --> 00:16:47.700
because they help us solve
those important problems.

00:16:47.700 --> 00:16:51.960
Anger, for example,
is a constellation,

00:16:51.960 --> 00:16:55.230
a package, of brain responses

00:16:55.230 --> 00:16:59.100
that facilitates our ability
to remove obstacles

00:16:59.100 --> 00:17:01.200
that are in the way
of important goals.

00:17:03.630 --> 00:17:06.630
DAMASIO:
With fear, the essential thing

00:17:06.630 --> 00:17:09.630
is to place the organism
out of danger.

00:17:09.630 --> 00:17:11.960
So for instance,

00:17:11.960 --> 00:17:16.460
an animal can rapidly flee
from the predator, or freeze.

00:17:18.960 --> 00:17:24.530
DAVIDSON:
And so the experience of certain
kinds of negative emotions

00:17:24.530 --> 00:17:27.860
are absolutely necessary
and appropriate.

00:17:27.860 --> 00:17:34.160
Where problems arise
is when an emotion persists

00:17:34.160 --> 00:17:38.700
for a much longer duration
of time than it normally would.

